cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS

This paper deals with supervised learning in the presence of an adversary who can corrupt a limited number of features in each instance. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper proposes subspace voting techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.AI), and also deals with datasets that involve image processing and signal analysis (cs.CV) and data structures (cs.DS).
